	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Belasco (Marvel Comics)</h1>
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		<div id="contentSub2"></div>
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#searchInput">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><table class="infobox" style="width:22em;width: 24em; background: #f2f9ff;"><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #99c2ff;">Belasco</th></tr><tr><td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:BELASCO_NEO.JPG" class="image"><img alt="BELASCO NEO.JPG" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/d6/BELASCO_NEO.JPG/250px-BELASCO_NEO.JPG" decoding="async" width="250" height="270" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/d/d6/BELASCO_NEO.JPG 1.5x" data-file-width="278" data-file-height="300" /></a><div>Belasco from <i>New X-Men</i> #37 by Niko Henrichon</div></td></tr><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;background: #99c2ff;">Publication information</th></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;"><a href="/wiki/Category:Comics_publishing_companies" title="Category:Comics publishing companies">Publisher</a></th><td><a href="/wiki/Marvel_Comics" title="Marvel Comics">Marvel Comics</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;"><a href="/wiki/First_appearance" title="First appearance">First appearance</a></th><td><i>Ka-Zar the Savage</i> #11. (Feb 1982)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;"><a href="/wiki/Category:Comics_creators" title="Category:Comics creators">Created by</a></th><td><a href="/wiki/Bruce_Jones_(comics)" title="Bruce Jones (comics)">Bruce Jones</a> (writer)<br /><a href="/wiki/Brent_Anderson" title="Brent Anderson">Brent Anderson</a> (artist)</td></tr><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;background: #99c2ff;">In-story information</th></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;">Team affiliations</th><td>Demons of Limbo<br />Elder Gods<br /><a href="/wiki/Cat_People_(comics)" class="mw-redirect" title="Cat People (comics)">Cat People</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;">Partnerships</th><td><a href="/wiki/S%27ym" title="S&#39;ym">S'ym</a><br /><a href="/wiki/Magik_(Illyana_Rasputin)" class="mw-redirect" title="Magik (Illyana Rasputin)">Darkchylde</a><br /><a href="/wiki/N%27astirh" title="N&#39;astirh">N'astirh</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;">Notable aliases</th><td>Lucifer</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;">Abilities</th><td>Skilled in magic<br />Invulnerability<br />Commands legion of demons</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p><b>Belasco</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Fictional_character" class="mw-redirect" title="Fictional character">fictional</a> <a href="/wiki/Supervillain" title="Supervillain">supervillain</a> appearing in <a href="/wiki/American_comic_book" title="American comic book">American comic books</a> published by <a href="/wiki/Marvel_Comics" title="Marvel Comics">Marvel Comics</a>. The character's first appearance was in <i>Ka-Zar the Savage</i> #11; he was created by <a href="/wiki/Bruce_Jones_(comics)" title="Bruce Jones (comics)">Bruce Jones</a> and <a href="/wiki/Brent_Anderson" title="Brent Anderson">Brent Anderson</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc" role="navigation" aria-labelledby="mw-toc-heading"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2 id="mw-toc-heading">Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
